review:
Today, 24th jan 2016, me and my wife decided not to visit AASTHA MEDICAL CENTRE again and we have the following feedback:

1) There is less or No coordination between the front desk support staff and Dr Shankutla. 
My wife treatment was going at AASTHA Centre with Dr Shakuntla. And she was not feeling well and From last three days she tried calling the reception so many times to collect and discuss about her reports which they had and the problems she is facing. And everytime the people at the front desk always telling that the doctor is busy and they will inform the doctor and we will arrange callback. But we never received any callback.
She tried calling Dr Shakuntla number as well and got the response that she will be given a callback in 10 minutes but no callback again.


2) Very Unprofessional behavior:

Since we are not getting any response so the fourth day i.e. on 24th Jan 2015 (Sunday) i called at the reception to book an appointment for us. The support staff at the reception booked an appointment for us 24th Jan 2015 (Sunday) 01:00 PM. And to our shock when we reached their the lady at the support staff very casually said the Dr Shankutla is busy and not available.
And you can take your reports.

My question is if the doctor is not available then:

a) How come you booked the appointment if Dr Shakunta was not available ?
b) And why didn't you informed the patient, even at the last minute, if there is no availability of Dr Shankutla ? Fortunately we are residing within 02 km range. Think if the patient is residing far.

My message to Dr Shakuntla

a) If you are charging your patient so high and in lieu of that they receive this kind of unprofessional service and behavior from you and your staff, then what's the difference in between Government and Private clinics?
b) I agree that being a doctor you might be very busy. But if on phone you said to callback in 10 mins then you should call the patient. Same goes with your support staff.

And we finally decided not the visit AASTHA MEDICAL CENTRE again.
reply_text: Thank you for your feedback madam.We are highly apologetic for the bad  experience you have had with us .We request you to give us an opportunity to be at your service again and we also promise to rectify the issues you have faced.

They didn’t even bother to inform before and I was standing in the rain because it’s so difficult to locate their clinic as well. 

Please keep your patients informed about the timings of the doctor or update the correct timings here as nobody has so much time, money and effort to waxte. I literally came and went back for nothing.

review: ** ********* ****** ***** ** *** **** ****** *** *** *** *** ***** Personalised practice and all relevant medical needs are available on every visit to her; besides she is always available in all the large corporate setups as well and we can get admitted there under her when needed, though we have always preferred Aastha Medical Centre for basic and short admissions as it is mush more hassle free and better in many ways. Insurance too doesn’t cause any reimbursement problems as far as I’ve experienced. Been taking care of my family for twenty years now !

Even though I’d say that the doctor is friendly and helpful in every way, the staff she employed at the reception are anything but. I don’t live in delhi and couldn’t collect the test results personally. The staff has made me call them repeatedly for my result email only to keep me waiting as they “forgot”. They have no responsibility towards the patient’s urgent need for the results and hang up on you when you call them. They most definitely have an attitude problem and start raising their voice when they have nothing better to say.

It has been one year when we visited doctor when I was only 6 weeks pregnant with high risk complications due to bleeding. Then I came to know about doctor Shukla through practo and we trusted her on the basis of the amount of experience and feedback provided on the practo site.
